This paper deals with modeling and mapping higher-order network flows, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) because the paper discusses mapping network flows in memory and multilayer networks, which are common in social and information networks. The second most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Software Engineering), as the paper discusses the use of Infomap, a software tool for mapping network flows. The third most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to simplify and highlight important dynamical patterns in complex systems. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper discusses the use of neural networks to model complex systems. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper discusses the use of algorithms to model and map network flows.
